===Verb===
{{en-verb|merchandis|ing}}

# {{context|intransitive|archaic|lang=en}} To engage in trade; to carry on [[commerce]].
#: {{rfquotek|Francis Bacon}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To engage in in-store promotion of the sale of goods, as by display and arrangement of goods.
#: ''He started his career '''merchandising''' in a small clothing store chain.''
# {{context|transitive|archaic|lang=en}} To [[engage]] in the trade of.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To engage in in-store promotion of the sale of.
#: ''He got hired to '''merchandise''' some new sporting goods lines.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To promote as if for sale.
#: ''The record companies don't get as good a return on '''merchandising''' artists under contract.''

